cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with weakly supervised object localization, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new method for solving this problem, which involves generating pseudo annotations and performing bounding box regression. This approach involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on two datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
